title: Independent candidate Aqib Ullah Khan wins PK-50 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Aqib Ullah Khan has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-50 Swabi-II by securing 40,870 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was PML-N candidate Babar Khan who bagged 21,089 votes.
Votersâ€™ turn-out remained at 40.81 per cent.
